The problem is the number of additional classes you need, but this can be resolved with a dynamic wrapper decorator. 
The Wrapper Decorator is a way to add interface implementation, methods and properties to already existing obejcts: [https://stackoverflow.com/questions/34595221/how-to-implement-a-wrapper-decorator-in-java][1]

In this way you need your `Visitor` interface and put there the `visit(L legacy)` methods:

